T9900-P4958-V1000-P2818-L128:WebService
T9900-P4958-V1003-P2818-L128:TenantWebService
T9900-P4958-X1-L999: Adding a new web service with the same Object Type and Service Name as an existing record
T9900-P4958-X2-L999: (system or tenant record) will result in a duplicate service error the same as today
T9900-P4958-X3-L999: =>  This scenario is covered by the PK on all tables involved.
T9900-P4958-X4-L999: We also want all of published services to have unique names whatever their Object Type is.
T9900-P4958-X5-L999: Otherwise, there is no difference in requesting, for example, page and query with the same Service Names
T9900-P4958-X6-L999: via OData, and metadata can not be generated.
T9900-P4958-X7-L999: Adding a new record for an Object (Type and ID) that has an unpublished system record
T9900-P4958-X8-L999: will give the following record/row error (Message:  The web service can't be added
T9900-P4958-X9-L999: because it conflicts with an unpublished system web service for the object.)
T9900-P4958-X10-L999: If the all tenants checkbox is selected, then create the web service record as a system
T9900-P4958-X11-L999: record, otherwise create as a tenant record
T9900-P4959-V1000-P2818-L128:WebService
T9900-P4959-V1001-P2818-L128:TenantWebService
T9900-P4959-X1-L999: Unselecting the all tenants checkbox will remove the system record and add a tenant record if one
T9900-P4959-X2-L999: doesn't already exist.
T9900-P4959-X3-L999: Selecting the all tenants checkbox will add a system record.
T9900-P4959-X4-L999: Changing the Object Type, Object ID, Service Name, and Publish fields of a system record will
T9900-P4959-X5-L999: change the value in the system record.
T9900-P4959-X6-L999: There is an existing record, so modify it.
T9900-P4959-X7-L999: There is no existing record, so insert one.
T9900-P4959-X8-L999: Changing the Object Type, Object ID, Service Name, and Publish fields of a tenant record will
T9900-P4959-X9-L999: change the value in the tenant record.
T9900-P4959-X10-L999: i.  Changing the web service to have the same Object Type and Service Name as an existing
T9900-P4959-X11-L999: record (system or tenant record) will result in a duplicate error the same as today.
T9900-P4959-X12-L999: =>  This scenario is covered by keys on the Web Service Aggregate table.
T9900-P4959-X13-L999: ii. Changing the web service to have the same Object (Type and ID) as an Unpublished system
T9900-P4959-X14-L999: record will give the following record/row error. (Message:  The web service can't be modified
T9900-P4959-X15-L999: because it conflicts with an unpublished system web service for the object.
T9900-P4960-V1000-P2818-L128:WebService
T9900-P4960-V1001-P2818-L128:TenantWebService
T9900-P4960-X1-L999: When deleting an existing web service record...
T9900-P4960-X2-L999: Deleting a tenant record will delete the tenant record.
T9900-P4960-X3-L999: Deleting a system record will delete the system record.
T9900-P4961-V1000-P2818-L128:WebService

T9900-P4961-X1-L999: Changing the Object Type, Object ID, Service Name, and Publish fields of a system record will
T9900-P4961-X2-L999: change the value in the system record.

T9900-P4961-X4-L999: change the value in the tenant record.

T9900-P4961-X6-L999: record (system or tenant record) will result in a duplicate error the same as today.

T9900-P4961-X10-L999: because it conflicts with an unpublished system web service for the object.

T50006-F7-P4962-X11-L999:

T50006-F7-P4962-X13-L999:  IF NOT(lSpecialOrderUtils.DefaultSPOFieldValuesSalesLine(Rec,SalesHeader,"Location Code",FALSE)) THEN BEGIN
T50006-F7-P4962-X14-L999:    IF NOT(CONFIRM(LSText04,FALSE,Type,"No.",SalesHeader."Store No.")) THEN
T50006-F7-P4962-X15-L999:      ERROR(LSText05)
